@page "/base-components"
<PageTitle>Base Components - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="base-components">Base Components</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                All Saascade components inherit from a hierarchy of base classes
                that provide common parameters, parent cascading, and design system integration.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h3>BaseComponent</h3>

            <p>
                The root abstract class. Provides these shared parameters:
            </p>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr><td>Id</td><td>string?</td><td>HTML id attribute.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Name</td><td>string?</td><td>Component name for form hierarchies.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Class</td><td>string?</td><td>Additional CSS classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Specialization</td><td>string?</td><td>Design system variant classes.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Style</td><td>string?</td><td>Inline styles.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Tooltip</td><td>string?</td><td>Tooltip text.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>AriaLabel</td><td>string?</td><td>Accessibility label.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>AriaLabelledby</td><td>string?</td><td>ID of the labelling element.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>AriaRole</td><td>string?</td><td>ARIA role attribute.</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>Parent</td><td>BaseComponent?</td><td>Cascading parent reference.</td></tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="child-content-variants">Child Content Variants</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Two subclasses extend BaseComponent with child content support.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h3>BaseComponentWithOptionalChildContent</h3>

            <p>
                Extends BaseComponent with an optional ChildContent render fragment.
                Use this as the base when child content is valid but not required.
            </p>

            <h3>BaseComponentWithRequiredChildContent</h3>

            <p>
                Extends BaseComponent with a required ChildContent render fragment via
                the EditorRequired attribute. Blazor will warn at compile time if child
                content is omitted on components that inherit from this class.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="name-hierarchy">Name Hierarchy</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The GetFullname method builds a dot-separated name path from the component
                tree — useful for semantic CSS targeting and form field naming.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Each component receives a cascading Parent reference from its ancestor.
                GetFullname recursively walks up the parent chain and concatenates Name values
                with dots. This lets you write CSS selectors against the data-fullname attribute
                to target specific components in a layout without class collisions.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="base-components-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Base Components</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Base Components</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                When Bootstrap 5 is the active design system, GetComponentName returns Bootstrap
                class names for each component type. The Specialization parameter accepts any
                Bootstrap modifier token such as btn-primary, card-header, or text-muted. The
                base class passes these values through to GetSpecializations in the Bootstrap 5
                design system, which appends them to the resolved base class.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="base-components-daisyui">DaisyUI Base Components</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Base Components</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                When DaisyUI is active, GetComponentName returns DaisyUI's semantic class names
                and GetSpecializations may return additional theme-aware classes such as
                bg-base-100 or shadow-sm. The base component infrastructure is identical across
                all frameworks — only the values returned by the design system differ. DaisyUI
                specializations are theme-sensitive and update when the active DaisyUI theme changes.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="base-components-basecoat">Basecoat Base Components</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Base Components</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                When Basecoat is active, GetComponentName and GetSpecializations return Tailwind
                utility class combinations curated by Basecoat. Because the base class infrastructure
                is framework-agnostic, switching from DaisyUI to Basecoat or vice versa requires
                only changing the registered IDesignSystem instance — no changes to component
                parameters or Razor markup are needed.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("base-components", "Base Components"),
    new TocItem("overview", "Overview", 2),
    new TocItem("child-content-variants", "Child Content Variants", 2),
    new TocItem("name-hierarchy", "Name Hierarchy", 2),
    new TocItem("base-components-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Base Components", 2),
    new TocItem("base-components-daisyui", "DaisyUI Base Components", 2),
    new TocItem("base-components-basecoat", "Basecoat Base Components", 2)
])" />

</div>
